The Edo State Commissioner for Arts, Culture and Diaspora Affairs, Osaze Osemwegie-Ero, has said that the state government has commenced the process of reviving cultural clubs in secondary schools across the state. Osemwegie-Ero, who disclosed this while speaking with journalists in Benin, said cultural clubs had already been inaugurated in secondary schools in Edo-South Senatorial District. He said similar events are being planned for secondary schools in Edo-North and Central districts to be held at St. John Modern College, Fugar, and Uromi Town Halls respectively by April this year. The commissioner said the Godwin Obaseki-led administration intends to inculcate cultural norms and values in students in secondary schools.  